---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro"
import Backbutton from "../components/Backbutton.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Line-ups">
    <Backbutton />
    <Card />
        <h1>Activities</h1>

        <div class="carousel_flip_container">
            <div class="carousel_inner">
                <div class="card active">
                    <div class="card_front">
                        <img src="img/activities_img/detektivskema.webp"
                            alt="Stemnings billede til detektivskema aktiviteten">

                        <h2>DETECTIVE SHEET</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card_back">
                        <p>"The Detective Sheet" is an educational resource designed for teaching about the
                            context
                            of
                            plants,
                            focusing on "foraging
                            sites" and "foraging landscapes."</p>

                        <p>
                            Before you begin: <br>
                            ᨒ Make sure to have your teacher print out the PDF or download it to your mobile
                            device.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Remember to bring a pencil and eraser if you're working on paper. <br>
                            ᨒ Keep the website, handy for reference, while completing the task. <br>
                            ᨒ Your teacher will allocate a specific amount of time for you to complete the
                            assignment.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Always remember to ask your teachers for guidance before foraging anything or if
                            you're
                            unsure
                            about
                            anything.
                        </p>

                        <p><a href="img/activities_img/9_Elev_Undervisningsforlob_-_Detektivskema.pdf" target="blank"
                                class="pdf">DOWNLOAD
                                PDF</a></p>

                        <img id="butterfly" src="img/activities_img/butterfly.svg" alt="butterfly illustration">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card_front">
                        <img src="img/activities_img/draw.webp" alt="Stemnings billede til draw the ingredient">

                        <h2>DRAW THE INGREDIENT</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card_back">
                        <p>"Draw the Ingredient" is an educational resource designed to teach about the unique
                            characteristics of ingredients and
                            plant identification. It's a simple drawing exercise intended to encourage students to pay
                            extra attention to specific
                            aspects of the ingredient. </p>


                        <p>
                            Before you begin: <br>
                            ᨒ Make sure to have your teacher print out the PDF or download it to your mobile
                            device.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Remember to bring a pencil and eraser if you're working on paper. <br>
                            ᨒ Keep the website, handy for reference, while completing the task. <br>
                            ᨒ Your teacher will allocate a specific amount of time for you to complete the
                            assignment.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Always remember to ask your teachers for guidance before foraging anything or if
                            you're unsure about anything.
                        </p>

                        <p><a href="img/activities_img/10_Elev_Undervisningsforlob_-_Tegn_Urten.pdf" target="blank"
                                class="pdf">DOWNLOAD
                                PDF</a></p>

                        <img id="flower" src="img/activities_img/flower.webp" alt="flower illustration">
                    </div>
                </div>


                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card_front">
                        <img src="img/activities_img/cook.webp" alt="Stemnings billede til cook the ingredient">

                        <h2>COOK THE INGREDIENT</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card_back">
                        <p>"Cook the Ingredient" is an educational resource aimed at enhancing students' understanding
                            of cooking ingredients and
                            culinary techniques. This activity encourages students to explore the unique characteristics
                            of ingredients and their
                            role in cooking.</p>


                        <p>
                            Before you begin: <br>
                            ᨒ Remember to wash hands thoroughly.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Always follow safety precautions when cooking.
                            <br>
                            ᨒ Read and understand the recipe carefully before you begin. Pay attention to ingredients,
                            measurements, and cooking
                            techniques. <br>
                            ᨒ Make sure you know how to use the right equipment. <br>
                            ᨒ Don't hesitate to ask your teachers for guidance if you're unsure about anything.
                        </p>

                        <p><a href="img/activities_img/10_Elev_Undervisningsforlob_-_Tegn_Urten.pdf" target="blank"
                                class="pdf">DOWNLOAD
                                PDF</a></p>

                        <img id="cook" src="img/activities_img/cookhat.svg" alt="cooking hat illustration">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <button class="btn prev">❮</button>
            <button class="btn next">❯</button>
            <div class="dots"></div>
        </div>   
</MainLayout>
